t clerics under his command. But, multiple times, he has demonstrated his comfort with disregarding recommendations from those advisers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/new-orleans-archbishop-gregory-aymond-protected-alleged-abusers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/first-thing-storms-in-us-north-east-wreak-havoc-and-leave-two-dead" target="_blank">First Thing: Storms in US north-east wreak havoc and leave two dead</a></h2><div class="description"> Triple-digit temperatures are persisting in the south of the US, from Arizona to Florida, with heat indexes as high as 115F. Extreme heat advisories remain active in several cities including Phoenix, Dallas, Houston, New Orleans and Orlando. “Same way a police officer would know deadly force was being used against the right people?”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:54:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/first-thing-storms-in-us-north-east-wreak-havoc-and-leave-two-dead" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/mega-millions-lottery-jackpot-prize-amount" target="_blank">Mega Millions lottery balloons to third-largest jackpot of $1.55bn</a></h2><div class="description"> Mega Millions lottery jackpot has grown to $1.55bn, making it the third-largest ever. No one has matched the game’s six winning numbers since 18 April, amounting to 31 straight drawings without a big winner. The prize has ballooned because no one has won the game's six numbers since April 18.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/mega-millions-lottery-jackpot-prize-amount" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/desantis-claims-agents-can-tell-traffickers-from-migrants-in-call-for-deadly-force" target="_blank">DeSantis claims agents can tell traffickers from migrants in call for deadly force</a></h2><div class="description"> Rightwing Florida governor and 2024 presidential hopeful Ron DeSantis has sparked controversy by outlining a hardline border policy of deadly force despite acknowledging that drug traffickers could be difficult to distinguish from migrants crossing into the US. Under his direction as president, US law enforcement on the lookout for drugs would not mistakenly use lethal force on migrants.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/desantis-claims-agents-can-tell-traffickers-from-migrants-in-call-for-deadly-force" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/san-diego-teens-arrested-killing-woman-pellet-gun" target="_blank">San Diego teens charged in killing of unhoused woman known as ‘Granny Annie’</a></h2><div class="description"> Two San Diego teenagers have been arrested in the fatal shooting of Annette Pershal, a 68-year-old unhoused woman. Pershal was found on the street unconscious on 8 May and taken to the hospital where doctors discovered she’d been shot multiple times with a pellet gun.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 00:58:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/san-diego-teens-arrested-killing-woman-pellet-gun" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/halt-taliban-repression-afghan-women-girls-education" target="_blank">The world must unite now to halt the Taliban’s repression of Afghan women and girls | Gordon Brown</a></h2><div class="description"> Two years of ever-intensifying repression have not dimmed the resilience of girls and women in Afghanistan. It is time to declare it a crime against humanity, and prosecutors of the international criminal court (ICC) should open an investigation into the repression. Afghanistan's permanent representative of Afghanistan to the U.N. has called it a 'gender apartheid'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</