 appropriate time.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:21:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/i-am-50-today-and-i-no-longer-care-what-anyone-thinks-about-my-age" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/will-donald-trump-be-jailed-before-trial" target="_blank">Will Donald Trump be jailed before his trial? | Robert Reich</a></h2><div class="description"> Former president continues to threaten witnesses despite warnings not to violate conditions of release. Judge Moxila A Upadhyaya warned him that he could be taken into custody if he violated the conditions of his release, including attempting to influence jurors or intimidate future witnesses. She called him ‘Mr Trump’ rather than President Trump – thereby emphasizing that he was being treated as any criminal defendant would be treated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 14:30:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/will-donald-trump-be-jailed-before-trial" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/08/conflict-of-interest-or-a-very-cunning-plan" target="_blank">Conflict of interest or a very cunning plan? | Fiona Katauskas</a></h2><div class="description"> The consultancy business 