09 Dec 2011 06:38:23 +0530</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">One India</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.oneindia.com/2011/02/26/punefc-take-on-in-form-vivakerala-aid0126.html" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/the-inhabitant-review-lizzie-bordens-evil-spirit-creeps-out-family-in-boilerplate-horror" target="_blank">The Inhabitant review – Lizzie Borden’s evil spirit creeps out family in boilerplate horror</a></h2><div class="description"> Director Jerren Lauder has levelled up his directing skills considerably since his debut feature. Odessa A’zion, who is insanely watchable in director’s American gothic tale. The Inhabitant evokes indie ‘elevated horror” features such as It Follows.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/the-inhabitant-review-lizzie-bordens-evil-spirit-creeps-out-family-in-boilerplate-horror" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/guardian-readers-cinema-etiquette-bad-behavior-anecdotes" target="_blank">‘I always confront’: Guardian readers on the decline of cinema etiquette</a></h2><div class="description"> Reader walked out of a showing of Barbie at the Odeon last week due to the behaviour of other people in the cinema – they were scrolling through phones, chatting as if they were in their own front room, waving their arms in the air during the musical number and whooping every time Ryan Gosling's face appeared on screen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 08:05:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/guardian-readers-cinema-etiquette-bad-behavior-anecdotes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/variety-review-fierce-feminist-porn-drama-from-the-80s-new-york-underground" target="_blank">Variety review – fierce feminist porn drama from the 80s New York underground</a></h2><div class="description"> Variety, directed by Bette Gordon, is re-released for its 40-year anniversary. It is a flawed but fascinating critique of the male gaze, the porn gaze and the luxurious ordeal of guilty voyeurism. Gordon casts a female lead, flipping gender assumptions and turning the tables on the underworld quest-torments of Paul Schrader’s male heroes in the likes of Taxi Driver and Hardcore.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/variety-review-fierce-feminist-porn-drama-from-the-80s-new-york-underground" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/william-friedkin-director-exorcist-french-connection-dies" target="_blank">William Friedkin created unforgettable horror and pleasure with equal brilliance</a></h2><div class="description"> The Exorcist and The French Connection director William Friedkin has died aged 87. Friedkin was a director who created so many visceral, unforgettable experiences for moviegoers. He was a film-maker who could offer films with the thrillingly intravenous excitement of hard drugs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:58:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/william-friedkin-director-exorcist-french-connection-dies" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/compassionate-spy-documentary-ted-hall" target="_blank">‘What people accused Oppenheimer of doing’: the untold story of spy Ted Hall</a></h2><div class="description"> Christopher Nolan’s blockbuster film, A Compassionate Spy, is about a lesser-known figure from the Manhattan Project. A young physicist, Ted Hall, isolated himself in the Army barracks after the Trinity Test. Oppenheimer would go on to hold grave misgives.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 18:06:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/compassionate-spy-documentary-ted-hall" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/jess-search-obituary" target="_blank">Jess Search obituary</a></h2><div class="description"> Jess Search, who has died aged 54 of brain cancer, did much to shape and inspire the world of documentary film. She sought to harness the power of non-fiction storytelling to bring about change on issues such as the climate crisis and defending democracy. The many dozens of films she funded, advised, mentored, distributed, produced or executive produced include Citizenfour and Virunga.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:38:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/jess-search-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/promising-young-woman-follow-up-london-film-festival-emerald-fennell" target="_blank">Promising Young Woman follow-up Saltburn given opening slot at London film festival</a></h2><div class="description"> Emerald Fennell’s film, starring Barry Keoghan, Jacob Elordi and Rosamund Pike, is ‘a tale of privilege and desire’ following a young student at Oxford. The writer-director has been selected as the opening film for the 2023 edition of the London film festival.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 11:00:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/promising-young-woman-follow-up-london-film-festival-emerald-fennell" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/kuwait-bans-hit-australian-horror-film-talk-to-me-over-casting-of-trans-actor-zoe-terakes" target="_blank">Kuwait bans hit Australian horror film Talk to Me over casting of trans actor Zoe Terakes</a></h2><div class="description"> Australian horror film Talk To Me has been banned from screening in Kuwait, reportedly solely over the casting of non-binary trans actor Zoe Terakes. Terakes plays a character whose gender identity is never mentioned in the film. The Hollywood Reporter first reported on the decision, which they confirmed was based entirely on the presence of Terakes, an Australian actor who identifies as trans-masculine.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 10:06:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/kuwait-bans-hit-australian-horror-film-talk-to-me-over-casting-of-trans-actor-zoe-terakes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/barbie-movie-tops-1bn-in-global-box-office-ticket-sales-breaking-record-for-female-directors" target="_blank">Barbie movie tops $1bn in global box office ticket sales, breaking record for female directors</a></h2><div class="description"> The movie took in $459m from North American theatres and another $572.1m overseas over the weekend, for a total of $1.0315bn (A$1.56bn, £800m) Barbie is now the biggest film to be directed by one woman, with director Greta Gerwig supplanting Patty Jenkins.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 01:01:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/07/barbie-movie-tops-1bn-in-global-box-office-ticket-sales-breaking-record-for-female-directors" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One review – Tom Cruise does it better</a></h2><div class="description"> Seven films in and nothing about M:I, from the star’s incredible stunt skills to the silly-serious tone, is showing any sign of slowing down. Already, the keynote stunt has become a legend: the one on the poster, the one he reportedly did – for real – six times in one day before he was satisfied.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 10:45:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/05/mission-impossible-dead-reckoning-part-one-review-tom-cruise" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">The Deepest Breath review – stunning Netflix documentary on freediving</a></h2><div class="description"> The Deepest Breath is a love story embedded in the world of free diving, the deadly extreme sport whose practitioners plunge toward the ocean floor, often wearing nothing but a wetsuit and nose plug. (Goggles are out of the question since the air pressure would cause blood vessels in the eyes to burst.)</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 10 Jul 2023 13:23:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/10/the-deepest-breath-review-stunning-netflix-documentary-freedriving" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Insidious: The Red Door review – shoddy horror sequel</a></h2><div class="description"> Patrick Wilson makes his directorial debut with a labored legacy sequel that should hopefully close the door on the long-running franchise. The unifying premise for hit factory Blumhouse’s reliable yet reliably uninteresting moneymaker dares viewers to wonder “what if there was a creepy thing that jumped out at you, then disappeared?”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/insidious-the-red-door-review-shoddy-horror-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Joy Ride review – slickly likable Asian-American comedy dwells on family and identity</a></h2><div class="description"> Writer-producer Adele Lim, who worked on the script for Crazy Rich Asians, now makes her feature directing debut with this likable and brash Asian-American comedy. The energy levels are high and there are some outrageous gags, between which the mandatory sentimentality is reasonably managed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 06 Jul 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/06/joy-ride-review-slickly-likable-asian-american-comedy-dwells-on-family-and-identity" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">The Out-Laws review – Pierce Brosnan can’t save limp Netflix comedy</a></h2><div class="description"> Adam DeVine plays a criminal father-in-law in an Adam Sandler-ushered action comedy that misses every time. The true Happy Madison stinkers are the ones even Sandler wouldn’t headline. The Out-Laws, courtesy of Happy Madison by way of Netflix, is a bundle of nice-guy nerves, a cartoon beta.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 07 Jul 2023 13:10:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/07/the-out-laws-review-pierce-brosnan-cant-save-limp-netflix-comedy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny review - Harrison Ford cracks the whip in taut sequel</a></h2><div class="description"> Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny is the fifth Indiana Jones film in which the legendary archaeologist and whip-cracking adventurer is back for another go-around. The film is the first not to be directed by Steven Spielberg - James Mangold is now at the helm.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 28 Jun 2023 16:44:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/indiana-jones-and-the-dial-of-destiny-review-harrison-ford-cracks-the-whip-in-taut-sequel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">No Hard Feelings review – Jennifer Lawrence comedy plays sex work for laughs</a></h2><div class="description"> Jennifer Lawrence plays Maddie, a woman in her early 30s who has been unlucky in love, who still lives in her childhood home, all alone since the death of her mo. The scene is Montauk in New York state, famously the location for the TV series The Affair.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 21 Jun 2023 12:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/21/no-hard-feelings-review-jennifer-lawrence-comedy-plays-sex-work-for-laughs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Elemental review – fire and water fall in love in multicoloured, unworldly Pixar fable</a></h2><div class="description"> The film is set in the city of four elements, with a message of acceptance in bricks of colour and concepts as if originated via algorithm. It is also a star-crossed love story based on that most traditional of American themes: melting-pot diversity in the big city.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 19 Jun 2023 12:00:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/19/elemental-review-fire-and-water-fall-in-love-in-multicoloured-unworldly-pixar-fable" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Fast X review – stupidly entertaining sequel offers more of the same</a></h2><div class="description"> The Fast &amp; Furious franchise reached the ideal level of sublime ridiculousness with Fast Five. The films that followed have tried nobly to top the simple, lizard-brain pleasure of this moment. Recent entries have started to grind like metal-on-metal, scrambling to figure out how to top itself.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 17 May 2023 16:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/17/fast-10-movie-review-fast-and-furious-sequel-vin-diesel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">White Men Can’t Jump review – comedy remake fumbles the shot</a></h2><div class="description"> A-story about the mobsters hunting for their vigorish? The R-rating for a comedy? No argument there. Teyana Taylor brings her true life experience as an NBA wife. The update, which premieres on Hulu, is an airball.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 18 May 2023 13:37:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/18/white-men-cant-jump-movie-review-jack-harlow" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">The Mother review – Jennifer Lopez goes kick-ass in abject kidnap thriller</a></h2><div class="description"> There's some real ChatGPT film-making here in this abjectly formulaic and inert Netflix thriller from director Niki Caro. Jennifer Lopez plays an ex-special forces parent aiming to rescues her kid from the bad guys. One villain (Gael García Bernal) disappears from the plot about halfway in.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 12 May 2023 01:00:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/may/12/the-mother-review-jennifer-lopez-netflix" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Why is Hollywood on strike (and why Succession’s Brian Cox is joining them)? - podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Production on Hollywood films and hit TV shows has ground to a halt because of the Sag-Aftra strike. Brian Cox, who played media boss Logan Roy in the TV series Succession, talks about why writers and actors can no longer make a living. Michael Safi speaks to a senior reporter with Guardian US, Lois Beckett and Brian Cox.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 15:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/audio/2023/aug/01/full-story-podcast-hollywood-actors-writers-strikes-sag-aftra-succession-brian-cox" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Why do Republicans hate the Barbie movie? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Christopher Nolan and Greta Gerwig starred in two of the year’s biggest movies. But conservatives have accused them of being too ‘woke’, anti-men and even Chinese propaganda. Is the outrage real or is it just another example of politics employing a culture war to rally the base? Jonathan Freedland and Amanda Marcotte try to figure out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/jul/28/why-do-republicans-hate-barbie-movie-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: actor Simon Pegg, Marina Hyde on the benevolent Lord Lebedev, and the truth about inflammation</a></h2><div class="description"> Simon Pegg on joining the A-list elite and embracing home life in Blighty. Marina Hyde implores us to ignore Lord Lebedev’s links to the KGB and just focus on his successes. Joel Snape reveals all you need to know about the hottest health topic: inflammation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 01 Jul 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/jul/01/weekend-podcast-actor-simon-pegg-marina-hyde-on-the-benevolent-lord-lebedev-and-the-truth-about-inflammation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Our critics’ guide to a summer of music, movies and culture - podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Guardian culture writers Alex Needham, Ellen E Jones and Michael Cragg make their picks of the best of this summer in arts and culture. Nosheen Iqbal hosts a guided tour of the summer in a weekly podcast from The Guardian. Read the full episode of the podcast here.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 05 Jun 2023 02:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/jun/05/our-critics-guide-to-a-summer-of-music-movies-and-culture-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: Little Mermaid star Halle Bailey, Marina Hyde on the This Morning ‘rift’, and the bereaved sex taboo</a></h2><div class="description"> Halle Bailey talks about overcoming self-doubt and her soulmate sister Chlöe. Author Kat Lister explores the stigma of grieving partners’ sexuality and the loss of sexual intimacy. Marina Hyde talks about Holly Willoughby and Philip Schofield’s alleged rift.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 20 May 2023 04:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/may/20/weekend-podcast-little-mermaid-star-halle-bailey-marina-hyde-on-the-this-morning-rift-and-the-bereaved-sex-taboo" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/barbies-muddled-feminist-fantasy-still-bows-to-the-patriarchy" target="_blank">Barbie’s muddled feminist fantasy still bows to the patriarchy</a></h2><div class="description"> Greta Gerwig’s fantasy comedy Barbie is ushering womankind on to the true path to sisterly empowerment. Toby Young has accused the film of “unapologetic misandry” while Critical Drinker has labelled it “most certainly a feminist film”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 12:18:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/barbies-muddled-feminist-fantasy-still-bows-to-the-patriarchy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">See no evil: why have baddies vanished from our cinema screens?</a></h2><div class="description"> Tom Cruise’s latest adversary is in fact a sentient computer code. Last summer, Top Gun: Maverick pulled off the same trick, ticking every crowdpleasing action-movie convention except one: it had no bad guy. An action movie without a real villain? Hans Gruber would be spinning in his grave.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 15:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/see-no-evil-why-have-baddies-vanished-from-our-cinema-screens" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Watership Down has been upgraded to a PG. That won’t stop it terrifying children | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> The 1978 animated version of Watership Down has been upgraded from U to PG (Parental Guidance) It is a remarkable example of censoring authority becoming more puritanical over time. The overwhelming threat of violence is part of what has made Watership down so compelling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 14:38:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/21/no-more-newborns-watership-down-has-been-upgraded-to-a-pg-itll-still-terrify-children" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Has Barbie killed the indie director? Credible film-makers are shamelessly selling out | Caspar Salmon</a></h2><div class="description"> Sarah Polley is set to direct the new ‘live-action’ reboot of Bambi. Polley has worked with Atom Egoyan, David Cronenberg and Hal Hartley before the age of 22. The film is set for release on Friday.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 10:42:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/19/barbie-indie-director-film-maker-greta-gerwig" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Latest Mission: Impossible shows the ‘silent Asian’ stereotype is alive and well</a></h2><div class="description"> Pom Klementieff’s supporting role as Paris, a savage assassin, is transformed into the tired stereotype of the silent Asian. The French actor, who is half Korean, barely utters a word throughout the whole thing. Paris is more than capable of giving Cruise's Impossible Mission Force agent, Ethan Hunt, a run for his money.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 17 Jul 2023 10:10:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/17/latest-mission-impossible-shows-the-silent-asian-stereotype-is-alive-and-well" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Jane Birkin: a tremendous screen presence with a gift for creative collaboration | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> Birkin made a sensational impact in Blow-Up, and went on to become a classy performer for a number of major French directors – notably Godard and Agnès Varda. She was a performer with that interesting distinction of being Anglo-French, which somehow added to her unlocatable quality.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 16 Jul 2023 17:22:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/16/jane-birkin-a-tremendous-screen-presence-with-a-gift-for-creative-collaboration" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">I did my PhD in Hollywood action films – here’s why Mission: Impossible is the best | Clem Bastow</a></h2><div class="description"> A major aspect of my PhD involved exploring the different ways in which Hollywood action films convey emotion through spectacle. Among the films I watched and rewatched were the Mission: Impossible films, which ended up being perhaps the key-est of my key works – for no other Hollywood franchise does action, or emotion, better.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 23:29:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/12/best-action-movie-franchises-mission-impossible" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Julian Sands: a hypnotically exotic actor full of style and extravagance</a></h2><div class="description"> After the smash hit of A Room With a View, Sands’ idiosyncrasies were hard to contain in mainstream movies, but in the right roles he was mesmerising. He was virtually impossible to cast as a conventional lead and almost as difficult as a character turn.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 21:30:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/27/julian-sands-an-hypnotically-exotic-actor-full-of-style-and-extravagance" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Academy, take action: why there should be an Oscar for best stunts</a></h2><div class="description"> The director of John Wick: Chapter 4 has revealed that he is in discussions with the Academy to officially recognise the power of action sequences. The Academy are in discussions to recognise action sequences as a form of formality. John Wick director says he is 'in discussions' with the film's producers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 15:15:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/22/oscars-best-stunts-john-wick" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Fierce, sensual, cerebral: how Glenda Jackson brought class to film | Peter Bradshaw</a></h2><div class="description"> The British actor was the epitome of countercultural chic in key 1970s films. It is just a shame she couldn’t be persuaded to do more of them when her political career ended. Jackson revered Eric and Ernie to the end of her life, because of her appearances on The Morecambe and Wise Show.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 14:03:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/15/fierce-sensual-cerebral-how-glenda-jackson-brought-class-to-cinema" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Chris Hemsworth thinks Thor has become ‘too silly’ – if superheroes are turning on Marvel, is endgame nigh?</a></h2><div class="description"> Three Marvel stars have recently broken rank to reveal that their movies sort of suck. They joke about being murdered by a sniper whenever an interviewer asks them anything even remotely spoilery. The tide has been slowly turning against the MCU, but at least Marvel could console itself with the knowledge that one group of people would never dare to badmouth it.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 12:47:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jun/07/marvel-actors-criticise-superhero-films-chris-hemsworth-elizabeth-olsen" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/07/one-hit-wonder-barbie-world-with-aqua" target="_blank">‘Critics wanted us to be a one-hit-wonder’: back in Barbie world with Aqua</a></h2><div class="description"> Aqua's take on Barbie pre-empted the hit film’s own subversion by 26 years. The Scandinavian pop group's sly, satirical take on the film's subversion has been noted some similarities. Aqua's male lead vocalist René Dif and keyboardist Søren Rasted looked at each other in elation and disbelief at a recent New York concert.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:41:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/07/one-hit-wonder-barbie-world-with-aqua" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/stardom-is-not-a-worthy-pursuit-julia-louis-dreyfus-on-sexism-ageing-and-fighting-fascism" target="_blank">‘Stardom is not a worthy pursuit’: Julia Louis-Dreyfus on sexism, ageing and fighting fascism</a></h2><div class="description"> Julia Louis-Dreyfus stars alongside Nicole Holofcener in new film You Hurt My Feelings. The pair met in the early 2010s to discuss whether she would star in the indie director’s next film. “We got along so well that I was kind of baffled we hadn’t met until then,” says Julia. ‘We would laugh until we peed. She would jump in with ideas that were generally fantastic’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/stardom-is-not-a-worthy-pursuit-julia-louis-dreyfus-on-sexism-ageing-and-fighting-fascism" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Victor Belmondo: ‘I wanted to be an actor – I never said to myself, yes, but that’s what Papi does too’</a></h2><div class="description"> Victor Belmondo, 29, has been quietly firing up his own acting career. He is unmistakably of the same lineage as his grandfather, Jean-Paul. He has a meaty supporting role in Lie With Me (Arrête avec tes)</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 14:03:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/03/victor-belmondo-i-wanted-to-be-an-actor-i-never-said-to-myself-yes-but-thats-what-papi-does-too" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">‘The lowest I’ve ever been’: how playing Jar Jar Binks led to abuse, near death – and saving Baby Yoda</a></h2><div class="description"> Ahmed Best was overjoyed when cast as Star Wars’s Jar Jar Binks – until the threats of violence began. As a podcast tells his story, he talks about hate, making movie history and a glorious comeback in The Mandalorian. TED-produced podcast tells the story of Ahmed Best.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 12:13:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/jul/28/star-wars-ahmed-best-interview-jar-jar-binks-the-phantom-menace-the-mandalorian" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">How did Barbie do it? Warner’s head of marketing on creating a ‘pink movement’</a></h2><div class="description"> The film broke box office records for the most commercially successful film by a female director. Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling roller-blading along Venice Beach as Barbie and Ken. The film brought in more than $356m worldwide during its opening weekend and another $50m on Monday and Tuesday alone.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 10:00:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/warner-bros-marketing-head-josh-goldstine-barbie-pink-movement" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">‘I was making a film about the trauma of an entire country’: director Alice Winocour on her movie about the 2015 Paris terror attacks</a></h2><div class="description"> Alice Winocour's brother Jérémie was caught up in the Bataclan siege. She wanted to address the events that had scarred France. She explains why she focused on the aftermath, not the violence, in her new film. The film-maker's younger brother was hiding in a back room at the concert hall.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 07:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/28/i-was-making-a-film-about-the-trauma-of-an-entire-country-director-alice-winocour-on-her-movie-about-the-2015-paris-terror-attacks" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">‘It’s a nonstop dream’: the YouTuber twins behind Talk to Me, the scariest film of the year</a></h2><div class="description"> Adelaide brothers Danny and Michael Philippou, AKA RackaRacka, have won the praise of Spielberg and Jordan Peele for their terrifying debut feature. Their horror film Talk to Me unleashed a competitive bidding war at this year’s Sundance film festival and landed them a seven-figure deal with A24.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 15:00:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/26/rackaracka-talk-to-me-film-danny-michael-philippou-youtube" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Talk to Me review – an Evil Dead for the Snapchat generation</a></h2><div class="description"> Danny and Michael Philippou’s feature debut is an entertaining chiller that mixes shrieking horror and psychological nuance. A sharp blend of psychological reality (bereavement, guilt), potent topicality (addiction, dependency) and phantasmagorial invention (a gateway to the beyond) packs a crowd-pleasing wallop without succumbing to quiet, quiet, LOUD jump-scare cliches.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 30 Jul 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/jul/30/talk-to-me-review-danny-and-michael-philippou-an-evil-dead-for-the-snapchat-generation-danny-michael-philippou" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/hypnotic-and-the-best-conspiracy-thrillers" target="_blank">Hypnotic and the best conspiracy thrillers</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Affleck's sci-fi thriller is a good jumping-off point for classic thrillers like JFK and Soylent Green. Audiences weren’t persuaded - it tanked in cinemas - but I think it has the makings of classic midnight-marathon fodder.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 05 Aug 2023 07:00:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/05/hypnotic-and-the-best-conspiracy-thrillers" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/wonder-woman-3-gal-gadot-dc-multiverse-week-in-geek" target="_blank">Amazonian prime: why Wonder Woman 3 will be the star of the new-look DC multiverse</a></h2><div class="description"> There has been a cull at DC under studio boss James Gunn, but Gal Gadot’s warrior princess stands tall, and her previously cancelled second sequel is back on. There is an alternate version of comic-book reality in which there is a major superhero cull, and Marvel's supervillains take eternal control of the Earth.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 11:36:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/04/wonder-woman-3-gal-gadot-dc-multiverse-week-in-geek" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/womens-world-cup-live-updates-jamaica-colombia-france-morocco/102703878" target="_blank">Live: Matildas watching France-Morocco game closely to find out World Cup quarterfinal opponent</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia beat Jamaica in Melbourne to set up a last-eight clash with England. Colombia will play France or Morocco in the quarterfinals of the FIFA Women's World Cup. Australia's Matildas will play either Morocco or France in the last eight. Colombia defeated Jamaica 1-0 in Melbourne on Tuesday night to reach quarterfinals.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:08:46 +0000</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">ABC Australia</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-08/womens-world-cup-live-updates-jamaica-colombia-france-morocco/102703878" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></di